threefourths of the impoverished nation is under water because 
wells and pumps are submerged people begin drinking flood water 
prompting a rise in diarrhea cases 
 
earthquakes 
aug 20 an earthquake registering 65 on the richter scale 
jolts the himalayan mountains foothills and plains of india and 
nepal it is the deadliest temblor in the region in 30 years at 
least 714 people are killed in nepal and 281 in india the official 
tolls are considered understated because the monsoons cut off roads 
to many remote villages tens of thousands of homes mostly of 
brick and mud are destroyed 
aug 6 an earthquake measuring 73 on the richter scale shakes 
burma bangladesh northern india and parts of pakistan and 
afghanistan four people die in india 
 
storms 
aug 16 a storm kills 1406 people and causes 12 billion in 
