a scaleddown version of a senateapproved 
bill authorizing a monument to american women who served in the 
vietnam war was approved thursday by a house subcommittee 
the senate bill approved 961 in midjune specifies that a 
bronze statue of an army nurse be erected on the 22acre grounds 
of the vietnam veterans memorial near the lincoln memorial 
but the measure approved thursday by the house administration 
subcommittee on libraries and memorials written as a substitute 
for the senate version says only that a monument to the 10000 
american women who served in vietnam can be built somewhere on 
federal land in the washington metropolitan area 
this will force separate votes by congress on a specific site 
and design for the monument as well as review by three federal 
agencies 
