canned goods and 1000 sacks of sorghum so far 
relief official eltayeb tahir told reporters a trainload of 
relief material arrived at elmeiram last monday and the transport 
ministry had been asked to allocate one train a week for the south 
thousands of southern sudanese displaced by civil war drought 
and recent floods have been moving north and many die of starvation 
or disease on the way 
on thursday a month after the floods the government said it 
estimates the damage to crops at about 365 million unofficial 
estimates put the cost much higher 
the rev aengus finucane director of the irish aid agency 
concern said last month 40 people were dying every day at 
elmeiram and starvation threatened about 2 million sudanese in the 
south 
according to alayams report the army stepped in when 
international relief groups said they could not move goods to the 
south because of the heavy rains and floods 
it did not mention the proximity of rebel sudan peoples 
liberation army forces besieging wau 160 miles from the elmeiram 
camp 
rebel gunners shot down two civilian planes in 1986 and 1987 and 
the insurgent army led by former col john garang has threatened 
to fire on relief planes the rebels claim the government uses 
civilian aircraft to move ammunition and troops 
garangs rebels began fighting the moslemdominated khartoum 
government in 1983 they seek autonomy for the south most of whose 
people are christians or animists and claim to control more than 
90 percent of the countryside 
