<TEXT>
the presidential campaigns of george bush and 
michael dukakis have tentatively agreed on sept 25 for the first 
debate between the two candidates a dukakis aide said thursday 
both debates will be general in subject matter in contrast to 
four years ago when the first was on domestic policy and the second 
covered defense and foreign policy said mark goodin bushs 
campaign spokesman 
paul brountas chairman of the dukakis campaign said the two 
contenders will face each other in a televised debate at wake 
forest university in winstonsalem nc 
brountas said their second debate would be either oct 13 or 14 
depending on the length of the american league baseball playoff 
series which will be televised in prime time 
the debate between vice presidential candidates dan quayle and 
lloyd bentsen is expected to take place during the week of oct 3 
the two campaigns have not reached agreement on the location for 
the second presidential debate and the vice presidential encounter 
he said 
we are still discussing format staging and the length of the 
debates and we will continue to carry on those discussions 
brountas said after meeting with bushs campaign chairman james a 
baker iii we believe we made good progress this will be an 
opportunity for the american people to see presidential candidates 
debating facetoface and mantoman 
the dukakis campaign wanted at least one more debate with the 
first to be on foreign policy and national security issues but 
that was rejected by the bush campaign 
brountas and baker emphasized that nothing is finally settled 
until they have agreed on all aspects of the debates 
but bush said thursday night it sounds very good got the 
right number 
additionally a statement released on air force two said i 
congratulate our negotiators on working out a formula for the 
number and timing of debates which certainly has my support 
on tuesday after weeks of negotiations the dukakis campaign 
said it was willing to accept the bush campaigns offer of two 
presidential debates as well as one encounter between quayle and 
bentsen 
the first debate will be sponsored by the national commission on 
presidential debates a group headed by the chairmen of the 
republican and democratic parties the commission also was likely 
to end up as sponsor of the vice presidential debate 
the league of women voters will sponsor the second presidential 
debate league president nancy neuman said the league is pleased 
that its now official that the american public will see at least 
one nonpartisan debate this fall 
she urged the campaigns to include the league in discussions on 
format last spring the league suggested 90minute debates with a 
single moderator rather than a panel of reporters such as used in 
past presidential debates 
goodin said the site of the second presidential debate would 
likely be on the west coast 
meanwhile nbc news president michael gartner issued a statement 
saying the network would not be able to televise the first debate 
live because it would conflict with its commitment to cover the 
olympic games 
nbc news will run a taped replay of the first presidential 
debate between george bush and michael dukakis that now has been 
scheduled for sunday sept 25 gartner said nbc has long been 
committed to broadcasting the olympics whose dates were known by 
both political parties 
