the justice department sued los angeles 
county and its top officials thursday alleging that the countys 
1981 redistricting plan has denied hispanics equal voting rights 
the lawsuit filed in us district court seeks to invalidate 
the electoral boundaries set for the countys five elected 
supervisors and to devise a new plan that complies with federal 
law 
