it doesnt seem quite right to use the word huge 
when talking about a minivan but thats the impression the 1988 
plymouth voyager le conveys 
it also is comfortable easy to drive and versatile 
want to take that antique table with two leaves and four 
chairs off aunt ruths hands pull out the two back seats of the 
van and tuck the dining set inside for the trip home no problem 
and the furniture wont get wet or dirty as it would in the 
back of a pickup during inclement weather have five young 
ballplayers to take to the park put the rear seats back in and 
theres room for equipment and another adult and no one is 
cramped 
its no wonder chrysler corp has sold more than 1 million of 
these littlebig gems since the automaker pioneered the minivan 
concept in the 1984 model year 
today bigger automakers such as toyota ford and general motors 
have joined the market but chrysler retains the sales lead 
toyotas van is sold in smaller quantities and has a higher base 
price for the cheapest passenger model about 13200 vs about 
11000 for a chrysler 
the ford and gm downsized vans are reardrive and a bit larger 
than chryslers one auto analyst has called the minivan the 
product success of this decade and some analysts predict annual 
industry sales of 1 million in the next decade 
chryslers idea for the minivan was to provide a fuelthrifty 
way to cart around passengers and cargo comfortably in a roomy 
vehicle that would drive like a car and fit in a garage like a car 
chrysler has stayed true to that concept as the test plymouth 
voyager le bore out it was easy to drive and felt like a car even 
during difficult parallel parking maneuvers 
driving in some other especially fullsize vans can give a 
distinct buslike feel as you turn the steering wheel and maneuver 
getting in and out of the voyager was uncomplicated compared with 
some other vans where you have to climb up to enter and take a 
flying leap to exit 
but like other vans and unlike a car the voyager 644 inches 
tall offered a good view of the road ahead i appreciated being 
