here is a summary of wednesdays developments in 
the federal investigation of insider trading 
the securities and exchange commission filed civil insider 
trading and stock manipulation charges against the investment firm 
drexel burnham lambert inc and michael milken the head of its 
junk bond trading unit gary lynch the secs director of 
enforcement said the allegations involved 18 series of 
transactions including 16 involving ivan boesky the former stock 
speculator now in prison 
stephen suikuan wang jr a former junior analyst at the 
investment firm morgan stanley amp co pleaded guilty in to the 
first criminal charges stemming from what the government has called 
wall streets second largest insider trading case wang is said to 
have stolen marketsensitive information about pending takeovers 
and sold it to a taiwanese businessman fred c lee who the 
government alleges used the information to make at least 19 
million on stock trades 
william dillon a former merrill lynch amp co stockbroker 
