<TEXT>
the proposed 25 billion merger of lucky 
stores inc and american stores co has been blocked temporarily by 
a federal judge as californias attorney general fought the plan he 
said would bring higher food prices to the state 
us district judge david kenyon who issued a temporary 
restraining order wednesday said he believed the acquisition of 
lucky supermarkets by american stores parent of the alpha betas 
supermarket chain threatens serious irreversible harm to 
californians 
kenyon scheduled a hearing sept 16 on whether to grant a 
preliminary injunction sought by california attorney general john 
van de kamp 
van de kamp who sued to prevent the merger says that 
transaction coupled with the recent acquisition of oaklandbased 
safeway stores by el montebased vons spells higher prices for 
consumers 
he said a survey he commissioned indicated the two mergers would 
increase food prices by 400 million a year in california 
american has said the merger of lucky with alpha beta would 
lower consumer food prices by 50 million annuallyu 
john lillie chairman of lucky stores inc in a statement said 
judge kenyons ruling was simply designed to maintain the status 
quo until a hearing on the merits of the case can be heard we are 
confident that the court will not want to delay the combination of 
alpha beta and lucky stores once we have the chance to lay out the 
facts before him 
the federal trade commission has tentatively approved the 
luckyalpha beta merger although it would require american to sell 
37 markets to competing chains to maintain competition 
nevertheless van de kamp wants a trial to decide whether the 
marriage of two supermarket giants is anticompetitive 
the proposed acquisition threatens serious irreversible harm 
to the public interest within california which outweighs any harm 
to defendants if the mergers are temporarily restrained kenyon 
said in imposing the temporary restraining order 
the judge forbade american stores from launching a joint 
operation with lucky stores until the matter is resolved in court 
the combination would give the alpha betalucky chain 550 stores 
van de kamp who has threatened similar court action in the 
vonssafeway merger said talks are progressing on reaching an 
outofcourt settlement of that dispute he praised kenyons 
decision on the luckyalpha beta proposal 
american stores did not immediately react to the developments a 
lucky spokeswoman referred calls to american 
in his ruling kenyon ordered american to refrain from selling 
transferring or closing any retail grocery stores in the areas 
where both american and lucky presently compete the judge said 
american must continue the operations of alpha beta independently 
of lucky stores and must refrain from supplying either with the 
assets of the other or exchanging confidential business information 
the restraining order barred american and lucky from entering 
into contracts which might hinder any future divestiture of the 
lucky assets 
kenyon also prohibited any change in the management team of 
lucky or of the american stores california operation 
americans attorney frank rothman had told the judge that the 
lucky management team was poised to take control of the joint 
operation 
in the earlier completed merger vons acquired 172 safeway 
stores which are in the process of being converted to vons 
operations vons will have 350 stores 
american which recently moved its headquarters from salt lake 
city to irvine calif is one of the nations largest supermarket 
companies its holdings include acme markets on the east coast 
skaggs alpha beta and alpha beta and buttery in the west and the 
27state osco drug chain 
